1:1 COMMENT "# generator_accepts_borrow.z -- bidirectional generator with a"
1:63 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# borrowed `accepts:`."
2:23 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# `accepts: Bag.lock` (or `.borrow`, or bare reftype) makes each"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# `.call value: bag.lock` deposit a borrowed pointer to the caller's"
5:69 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# Bag into the synth class's `_resume_input` slot. The lock is held"
6:68 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# for the duration of the call; on resumption, `name: yield v`"
7:63 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# binds `name` as a pointer alias into the caller's storage, so"
8:64 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# `name.x` reads the LIVE field through the lock."
9:50 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#"
10:2 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# Liveness rule: `name` is valid only until the NEXT yield. Using"
11:66 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# it past that point would read a different .call's caller storage"
12:67 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# (or stale data on a follow-up resumption). The typechecker"
13:61 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "# rejects such uses with a hint pointing at `.take` for the"
14:60 EOL "\n"
15:1 COMMENT "# store-across-yields case."
15:28 EOL "\n"
16:1 EOL "\n"
